{"timestamp": "2025-12-16 15:13:16.382417", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: **Anomaly detected**\\n\\n- **Host:** `host_2_1_1_1` (10.2.1.1)  \\n- **Symptom:** All ping attempts from this host to any other machine (including the DNS server) return *“Network is unreachable”*.\\n\\n**Localization**\\n\\n- The ping trace shows that the host can reach its own IP (10.2.1.1) but cannot reach the gateway or any external address.\\n- The network configuration for `host_2_1_1_1` confirms the problem:\\n\\n  | Field | Value |\\n  |-------|-------|\\n  | `ifconfig` | `eth0` is up, but no `inet` address is shown. |\\n  | `ip_addr` | No global IP address is listed for `eth0`. |\\n  | `ip_route` | Empty – no default route or any route entries. |\\n\\n**Root cause**\\n\\n`host_2_1_1_1` has not been assigned a valid IPv4 address on its `eth0` interface, and consequently it has no default gateway configured. Without an IP address and a default route, the kernel cannot forward packets to the rest of the network, which is why the ICMP packets fail with “Network is unreachable”.\\n\\n**Next steps (not requested but useful)**\\n\\n1. Assign a proper IP address to `eth0` (e.g., `10.2.1.1/24`).  \\n2. Add a default route pointing to the router for the 10.2.0.0/24 subnet (e.g., `ip route add default via 10.2.1.1 dev eth0`).  \\n3. Verify connectivity again with `ping` or `traceroute`.\\n\\nOnce the interface is correctly configured, `host_2_1_1_1` will be able to communicate with the rest of the network., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='36ecd4e0-00f9-463d-af82-42c01b6701c4'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "not_implemented", "id": ["langchain_ollama", "chat_models", "ChatOllama"], "repr": "ChatOllama(model='gpt-oss:20b', validate_model_on_init=True, temperature=0.0, base_url='http://10.68.186.140:11434')", "name": "ChatOllama"}}
